And the addicted to quack guys get an A+ in my book for writing this:

While it hasn't appeared this way in the win column, Mike Leach has their program going in a good direction and has dramatically improved the talent in Pullman over his tenure. The Cougars aren't the pushovers fans have come to expect and we need to move past our recent historical views on Pullman. Sure, we can make excuses for Oregon's performance but the reality is that this Washington State team is competitive in a very tough Pac-12. It took an otherworldly performance by a Heisman candidate quarterback to escape Pullman with a win. Time to adjust our perspective
